================================================================
PRACTICAL NO. 10 - LOGGING, SCREENSHOTS, STATE MACHINE & PUBLISH
================================================================

PRE-REQUISITES:
- UiPath Studio installed
- UiPath Orchestrator account (free Community edition at cloud.uipath.com)
  (Required only for 10(c) - Publish)
- Any application to automate (Notepad works for all parts)

================================================================
PRACTICAL 10(a) - Automate Process Logging and Taking Screenshots
================================================================

DIFFICULTY: Easy

WHAT YOU WILL DO:
You will create a workflow that:
1. Logs messages at different stages (Info, Warning, Error levels)
2. Takes and saves a screenshot automatically during the workflow

--- STEP-BY-STEP INSTRUCTIONS ---

PART 1 - LOGGING

Step 1: Open Notepad on your computer.

Step 2: Open UiPath Studio → New Project.
  - Name it: Practical_10a_LoggingScreenshots
  - Click Create

Step 3: From the Activities panel, search "Log Message" and drag it 
        into the Main sequence.

Step 4: In the Log Message properties:
  - Level: Info
  - Message: "Workflow started - Practical 10a"

Step 5: After the Log Message, drag an "Open Application" or 
        "Type Into" activity (we'll just use Type Into on Notepad).
  - Drag "Type Into" → Indicate Notepad text area
  - Text: "Hello from UiPath!"

Step 6: Add another "Log Message" after the Type Into.
  - Level: Info
  - Message: "Text typed into Notepad successfully."

Step 7: Drag one more "Log Message".
  - Level: Warn
  - Message: "This is a warning log — check if Notepad is saved."

Step 8: Run (F5).
  - After the run, look at the OUTPUT PANEL at the bottom of UiPath Studio.
  - You will see all your log messages with timestamps and levels.
  - Info → blue  |  Warn → yellow  |  Error → red

Step 9 (Bonus — Log to File):
  - You can also log to a text file using a "Write Text File" activity.
  - Before each important step, add:
    Drag "Write Text File"
      FileName: "C:\Users\YourName\Desktop\log.txt"
      Text: "[" + Now.ToString + "] Step completed"
      Append: True (check this so each log adds to the file, not overwrites)

PART 2 - SCREENSHOTS

Step 10: From Activities, search "Take Screenshot" and drag it 
         into the sequence (after one of the Type Into steps).

Step 11: In Take Screenshot properties:
  - Drag it AFTER your "Type Into" activity so it captures the state.
  - Output → Image: press Ctrl+K → name it: screenImg

Step 12: After Take Screenshot, drag "Save Image" activity.
  - Image: screenImg
  - FileName: "C:\Users\YourName\Desktop\screenshot_" + Now.ToString("yyyyMMdd_HHmmss") + ".png"
  - This saves the screenshot with a timestamp in the filename.

Step 13: Add another "Log Message" after Save Image.
  - Level: Info
  - Message: "Screenshot saved to Desktop."

Step 14: Run (F5).
  - Check your Desktop → a PNG screenshot file should be saved there.
  - The Output panel shows all log messages.

FULL SEQUENCE SUMMARY:
  [Log Message - "Workflow started"]
  [Type Into - Notepad]
  [Log Message - "Text typed"]
  [Take Screenshot]
  [Save Image]
  [Log Message - "Screenshot saved"]
  [Log Message - "Workflow completed"]

